ASSETS LICENSE

This file covers the 3D body assets only. The application code is covered by
the MIT license in LICENSE.

public/assets/body-a.glb and public/assets/body-b.glb are human meshes
generated with MPFB2 (v2.0.16, the MakeHuman plugin for Blender,
makehumancommunity.org) via the reproducible pipeline in scripts/
(setup-mpfb.py -> generate-bodies.py -> verify-bodies.mjs). Per the
MakeHuman community's licensing policy, characters exported from
MakeHuman/MPFB are CC0: no attribution or share-alike obligation applies
to these meshes. The MPFB2 software itself is GPL-licensed; it is not
distributed in this repository (the setup script downloads it at build
time).

public/assets/body-neutral.glb is a placeholder primitive blob generated by
scripts/make-placeholder-body.mjs, original to this repository, MIT like the
rest of the code.

If a future asset derives from CC BY-SA anatomy sources (BodyParts3D,
Z-Anatomy, Open3DModel), it will ship under CC BY-SA and this file will
carry the attribution text.
